dismissalText.commentary: Daniel Vettori b Harris 70 (49b 8x4 2x6 79m) SR: 142.85

commentTextItems.html: steps to the off side and he tries to glance it, but misses and loses his off stump - Australia wins the game and levels the series at one apiece

commentPostTextItems.html: What a finish - full credit to the Aussies for getting over the line, another great game of 50 over cricket in the battle for the Chappell Hadlee trophy. Smart bowling in the end from Harris got the Aussies home when it looked like it was going to go the other way. Player of the match was Dan Vettori for his excellent bowling and bold batting - sadly his innovative batting was his undoing. Great to watch though.

These teams appear to be very well matched up and they will meet again on Tuesday at the lovely Seddon Park in Hamilton for the 3rd ODI. On behalf of the team this is Lawrie Colliver signing off - make sure you join us on Tuesday from Hamilton

commentPreTextItems.html: Harris to crank it up for Australia

commentTextItems.html: drives at a wide length ball, edging to 3rd man, did well there the lad. Now Vettori on strike with 13 off 11 balls required
edges on the bounce just short of slip, Haddin dives tries to catch it, White knocks it down and a single is scored

commentPostTextItems.html: What tension ------ ten from the over for the Kiwis. Maybe a dot ball might have been better there for the Kiwis, as Vettori would have had the strike

commentTextItems.html: late inswinger, hits him on the pad but angling down leg
makes room and hammers a drive to mid off, no chance of a run as he hit it far too well
moves to the off side and tries to flick a length ball that goes over the top of middle................gee that was close
backs away to leg again and lofts it over mid off.......just and it runs away for another four!!!! Great stuff from the skipper!
makes room and drives a low full toss on middle stump through cover point, unbelievable shot!!!!
full again, he digs it out behind the stumps to keep the strike - ending an excellent over for the Aussies
another yorker, he makes room but misses again

commentPostTextItems.html: Harris just needs to get one on the stumps here...................perhaps?

commentTextItems.html: moves to leg and tries to hit a yorker, no contact
has a wild swing at a good length ball and gets an edge to 3rd man, bit of panic in that shot - but got away with it

commentPostTextItems.html: Now can Vettori keep his head..................

commentTextItems.html: plays back and is beaten outside off - good bowling

commentPostTextItems.html: single needed here by Southee to get his skipper on strike

commentPreTextItems.html: Interesting, with six in the circle Southee is going to need to take score a single somehow. Harris back to bowl

commentTextItems.html: comes forward in defence, fielded by the bowler
works to long leg - so Southee will have the strike

commentPostTextItems.html: Now it's time for the batting powerplay with just  4 overs left this match

headshotImage.caption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: defends off the back foot back to the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: one more ball to survive for Southee

commentTextItems.html: flashes at a wide ball outside off and misses it

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Bond b Johnson 6 (12b 1x4 0x6 17m) SR: 50

commentTextItems.html: very full and he plays inside it and he loses his stump -- well bowled by Johnson, at last a bowler goes full and straight and it has paid off

commentPostTextItems.html: Southee is the new man in, can he stay with his skipper and guide NZ to a 2-nil lead in this series?

commentTextItems.html: cuts to 3rd man again, this time along the ground for a single

commentPostTextItems.html: 27 off 28 now required, could NZ be favourites?

commentTextItems.html: full and leg side, a shocker of a ball and another run for NZ

Haddin has positively laced that drive after taking a couple of steps down the pitch, it flew wide of Vettori but he thrust his left hand out and somehow it stuck. That ball was seriously well struck, great stuff from Vettori.
